    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI'm making a UI for neovim, and noticed that using `--listen` with `--headless` makes long printed messages display weird. The message window is not focused, and jumps to the end. Happens both with and without multigrid.\r\n\r\nHere I run the neovim instance with and without `--headless` and connect my UI to both. I do `lua vim.print(vim.fn.api_info())` to print a long message, and with `--headless` everything is messed up. When I use `k` to scroll up it keeps printing the same thing.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/83525937/e67c1ea7-9fcc-4ca4-adb0-52163f91a567\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --listen localhost:6666 --headless`\r\n2. Connect ui to port\r\n3. Run `:lua vim.print(vim.fn.api_info())`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nMessage displays correctly\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2604+g59aadf33e-Homebrew\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.3.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\ntmux\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nhomebrew",
